title: Britam Defence leaked information
description:
In late 2012 JAsIrX hacked the network of British defence contractor Britam Defence.  He posted a set of six .rar files containing sensitive information pertaining to deals between defence contractors and governments and the stability of the Middle East and many internal emails.  Subsequently, the files became very difficult to find because most of the filehosts stopped making them available.  After a great deal of effort, snooping around, trying links and research I finally found what I think is the original archive (after comparing its contents to news articles talking about the hack and the information inside).

Files contained within Britam.Defence.rar:

Britam Defence/arch11.rar
Britam Defence/arch1_locked.rar
Britam Defence/arch22.rar
Britam Defence/arch2_locked.rar
Britam Defence/arch33.rar
Britam Defence/arch3_locked.rar
Britam Defence/Leaked Documents.txt

Start looking in arch33.rar.
